 If the execution of a query is depending on the result of another query, it is called as sub-query.
 
 The dependent query is the main query & the other query is called as sub-query.
 
 Among the main query & sub query, the sub-query will be executed first.
 
 If nested sub-queries exist, then the innermost sub-queries will be executed first.
 
 Classification of sub-queries:
 
 1. Based on execution 
    > Single column - Single row 
    > Single column - Multi row 
    > Multi column - Single row 
    > Multi column - Multi row 
    
 2. Based on Usage
    > Normal Query
    > Co-related Query
    
